1.content:
Magic: Magic is rare. Magic ability is INBORN, Magic is NOT a choice. Magic is neither good nor evil;
Mana: Magical stamina. ONLY mages are born with mana. Mana roots from the distinctive soul of a mage;
"Mana Cull": Difficult runic inscription that forcibly extracts all mana from a mage, KILLING the mage because it is equivalent to extracting the root of mana which is the mage soul. Although illegal, culled mana is sold on black market or alchemized for magical artifacts;
Rune Magic: Runic inscriptions hold innate power. Not require mana or inborn ability;

2.content:
Kingdom: Jale, capital of Relvon. Jale began as a mining town long ago;
Background: Magic is feared and outlawed due to some disruption half century ago;

Black Market: Near a waterport of Jale, inner part of city slums (lowest class and poverty area). "A treacherous cesspool". Culled mana is popular among the highborns;

The Underside: "A big lovely hole in the ground". Outside the city (crumbling wall region) in the far mountainsides. The Underside is an underground region of abandoned mines, now home to outcasts, renegades, criminals, runaways, some mages. Honor among thieves, Reputation system. Interconnection of tunnels and caves and dwellings of rock and mud. Underground river that leads to Jale's slums, smuggle route;

Trinket Market: Large trinket market of stolen and odd goods is located in a grand hollowed area at heart of Underside, overhead shaft (Culled mana is not welcomed at the trinket market since Underside harbors mages).

